Passengers will be asked to make smart phones, tablets and other devices in the flight mode.
That is still not "Words With Friends," a scrabble extensive online game, which the actor Alec Baldwin played on his smartphone in 2011, when he had to leave an American Airlines jet high profile, because he refused to shut down the device, while the plane was parked at the gate.
And heavier devices such as laptops must continue to be stored, because there is a risk of injury if they fly through the cabin.
Mobile phone calls during the flight will also remain banned.
The regulatory competence for telephone calls lies with the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), not the FAA.
